    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A phrase describing how a term should be used and/or a citation to a work which uses it. May also include other kinds of examples that facilitate immediate understanding, such as widely know prototypes or instances of a class, or cases where a relation is said to hold.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">描述如何使用术语的短语，和/或引用使用该术语的作品。还可能包括其他有助于立即理解的示例，如广为人知的原型或类的实例，或关系成立的情况。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">GROUP:OBI:&lt;http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi&gt;</obo:IAO_0000119> <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="zh">组:OBI:&lt;http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi&gt;</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">example of usage</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">用法示例</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">example of usage</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">用法示例</rdfs:label>
    </owl:AnnotationProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115 -->

    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">The official OBI definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property. Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">官方的OBI定义，解释类或属性的含义。应是亚里士多德式的、形式化和规范化的。可辅以通俗定义。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">The official definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property. Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">官方定义，解释类或属性的含义。应是亚里士多德式的、形式化和规范化的。可辅以通俗定义。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">2012-04-05: 
Barry Smith

The official OBI definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property: 'Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions'  is terrible.

Can you fix to something like:

A statement of necessary and sufficient conditions explaining the meaning of an expression referring to a class or property.

Alan Ruttenberg

Your proposed definition is a reasonable candidate, except that it is very common that necessary and sufficient conditions are not given. Mostly they are necessary, occasionally they are necessary and sufficient or just sufficient. Often they use terms that are not themselves defined and so they effectively can't be evaluated by those criteria. 

On the specifics of the proposed definition:

We don't have definitions of 'meaning' or 'expression' or 'property'. For 'reference' in the intended sense I think we use the term 'denotation'. For 'expression', I think we you mean symbol, or identifier. For 'meaning' it differs for class and property. For class we want documentation that let's the intended reader determine whether an entity is instance of the class, or not. For property we want documentation that let's the intended reader determine, given a pair of potential relata, whether the assertion that the relation holds is true. The 'intended reader' part suggests that we also specify who, we expect, would be able to understand the definition, and also generalizes over human and computer reader to include textual and logical definition. 

Personally, I am more comfortable weakening definition to documentation, with instructions as to what is desirable. 

We also have the outstanding issue of how to aim different definitions to different audiences. A clinical audience reading chebi wants a different sort of definition documentation/definition from a chemistry trained audience, and similarly there is a need for a definition that is adequate for an ontologist to work with.</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">2012-04-05: 
Barry Smith

官方的OBI定义，解释类或属性的含义：'应是亚里士多德式的、形式化和规范化的。可辅以通俗定义' 很糟糕。

你能改成类似这样吗：

一个必要且充分条件的陈述，解释指代类或属性的表达式的含义。

Alan Ruttenberg

你提议的定义是一个合理的候选，但常见情况是并未给出必要且充分条件。大多数时候是必要条件，偶尔是必要且充分或仅仅充分。它们经常使用未定义的术语，因此实际上无法用这些标准来评估。

关于提议定义的具体问题：

我们没有'含义'、'表达式'或'属性'的定义。对于预期意义上的'指称'，我认为我们使用术语'外延'。对于'表达式'，我认为你是表示符号或标识符。对于'含义'，它因类和属性而异。对于类，我们需要文档让预期读者能够判断一个实体是否为该类的实例。对于属性，我们需要文档让预期读者在给定一对潜在关系项时，判断该关系成立的断言是否为真。'预期读者'部分建议我们也要指定我们认为能够理解定义的人，并推广到人类和计算机读者，包括文本定义和逻辑定义。

个人而言，我更倾向于将定义弱化为文档，并说明理想的做法。

我们还有一个未解决的问题：如何针对不同受众提供不同的定义。阅读chebi的临床受众需要与受过化学训练的受众不同类型的定义文档/定义，同样，也需要一个足以让本体学家使用的定义。</obo:IAO_0000116>
