        <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="en">Assay the wavelength of light emitted by excited Neon atoms. Count of geese flying over a house.</obo:IAO_0000112> <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="zh">测定激发态氖原子发射的光的波长。计数飞过房屋的鹅群。</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A planned process that has the objective to produce information about a material entity (the evaluant) by examining it.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">一种计划性过程，其目标是通过检查物质实体（被评估者）来产生关于它的信息。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">12/3/12: BP: the reference to the 'physical examination' is included to point out that a prediction is not an assay, as that does not require physical examiniation.</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">2012年12月3日：BP：提到‘体检’是为了指出预测不是测定，因为预测不需要身体检查。</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Discussion on OBI call 2023-05-01 resulted in an agreement to revise the textual definition of 'assay'.  https://github.com/obi-ontology/obi/issues/1683.</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">在2023年5月1日的OBI电话会议上的讨论达成一致，修订‘测定’的文字定义。https://github.com/obi-ontology/obi/issues/1683。</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">OBI branch derived</obo:IAO_0000119> <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="zh">OBI分支派生</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">assay</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">测定</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000202 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000202">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="en">The person perform microarray experiments and submit microarray results (including raw data, processed data) with experiment description to ArrayExpress.</obo:IAO_0000112> <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="zh">该人员执行微阵列实验并将微阵列结果（包括原始数据、处理数据）及实验描述提交至ArrayExpress。</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">一种由实体承担的角色，该角色在实现目标的研究过程的一部分中被实现。这些过程包括：规划、监督、资助、评审等。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Implementing a study means carrying out or performing the study and providing reagents or other materials used in the study and other tasks without which the study would not happen.</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">实施研究意味着执行或进行该研究，并提供研究中使用的试剂或其他材料以及其它任务，没有这些任务研究将无法进行。</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Philly2013: Historically, this role would have been borne only by humans or organizations. However, we now also want to enable representing investigations run by robot scientists such as ADAM (King et al, Science, 2009)</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">Philly2013：历史上，这种角色只由人类或组织承担。但现在我们也希望能够表示由机器人科学家（如ADAM，King等，《科学》，2009）进行的研究。</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">OBI</obo:IAO_0000119> <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="zh">OBI</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <obo:IAO_0000232>Feb 10, 2009.  changes after discussion at OBI Consortium Workshop Feb 2-6, 2009.  accepted as core term.</obo:IAO_0000232>
        <rdfs:comment>Philly2013: Historically, this role would have been borne only by humans or organizations. However, we now also want to enable investigations run by robot scientists such as ADAM (King et al, Science, 2009)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">investigation agent role</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">研究代理角色</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000245 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000245">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="en">PMID: 16353909.AAPS J. 2005 Sep 22;7(2):E274-80. Review. The joint food and agriculture organization of the United Nations/World Health Organization Expert Committee on Food Additives and its role in the evaluation of the safety of veterinary drug residues in foods.</obo:IAO_0000112> <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="zh">PMID: 16353909.AAPS J. 2005 Sep 22;7(2):E274-80. Review. 联合国粮食及农业组织/世界卫生组织食品添加剂联合专家委员会及其在评估食品中兽药残留安全性方面的作用。</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">An entity that can bear roles, has members, and has a set of organization rules. Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">一种可以承担角色、拥有成员并有一组组织规则的实体。组织的成员可以是组织本身或个人。成员可以承担由组织规则确定的特定组织成员角色。组织规则还决定了组织成员如何代表组织做出决策。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">BP: The definition summarizes long email discussions on the OBI developer, roles, biomaterial and denrie branches. It leaves open if an organization is a material entity or a dependent continuant, as no consensus was reached on that.  The current placement as material is therefore temporary, in order to move forward with development. Here is the entire email summary, on which the definition is based:

1) there are organization_member_roles (president, treasurer, branch
editor), with individual persons as bearers

2) there are organization_roles (employer, owner, vendor, patent holder)

3) an organization has a charter / rules / bylaws, which specify what roles
there are, how they should be realized, and how to modify the
charter/rules/bylaws themselves.

It is debatable what the organization itself is (some kind of dependent
continuant or an aggregate of people). This also determines who/what the
bearer of organization_roles' are. My personal favorite is still to define
organization as a kind of 'legal entity', but thinking it through leads to
all kinds of questions that are clearly outside the scope of OBI.

Interestingly enough, it does not seem to matter much where we place
organization itself, as long as we can subclass it (University, Corporation,
Government Agency, Hospital), instantiate it (Affymetrix, NCBI, NIH, ISO,
W3C, University of Oklahoma), and have it play roles.

This leads to my proposal: We define organization through the statements 1 -
3 above, but without an 'is a' statement for now. We can leave it in its
current place in the is_a hierarchy (material entity) or move it up to
'continuant'. We leave further clarifications to BFO, and close this issue
for now.</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">BP：该定义总结了关于OBI开发者、角色、生物材料和denrie分支的长期电子邮件讨论。它未确定组织是物质实体还是依赖持续体，因为尚未达成共识。因此，目前将其归类为物质是暂时的，以便推进开发。以下是定义所依据的完整电子邮件摘要：

1) 存在组织成员角色（主席、财务主管、分支编辑），以个人为承载者

2) 存在组织角色（雇主、所有者、供应商、专利持有人）

3) 组织有章程/规则/细则，规定有哪些角色、如何实现以及如何修改章程/规则/细则本身。

组织本身是什么（某种依赖持续体或人的集合）存在争议。这也决定了组织角色的承载者是谁/什么。我个人仍倾向于将组织定义为一种‘法律实体’，但深入思考会引出各种明显超出OBI范围的问题。

有趣的是，只要我们能对组织进行子类化（大学、公司、政府机构、医院）、实例化（Affymetrix、NCBI、NIH、ISO、W3C、俄克拉荷马大学），并让其扮演角色，组织本身的位置似乎并不重要。

由此我提出建议：我们通过上述陈述1-3定义组织，但目前没有‘is a’语句。我们可以将其保留在当前的is_a层次结构（物质实体）中，或上移至‘持续体’。我们将进一步的澄清留给BFO，并暂时关闭此问题。</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">GROUP: OBI</obo:IAO_0000119> <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="zh">组：OBI</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">organization</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">组织</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000260 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000260">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000017"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000104"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="en">The plan of researcher X to perform an experiment according to a protocol.</obo:IAO_0000112> <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="zh">研究员X根据方案执行实验的计划。</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A plan is a realizable entity that is the inheres in a bearer who is committed to realizing it as a completely executed planned process.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">计划是一种可实现的实体，内在于一个承诺将其作为完全执行的计划过程来实现的承载者。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">This class is included to make clear how the plan specification, the plan, and the planned process relate. OBI will however only subclass and work under the 'plan specification', and 'planned process' class, as we want to avoid to get deep into discussions of 'intend' etc.</obo:IAO_0000116> <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="zh">包含此类是为了明确计划规范、计划和计划过程之间的关系。然而，OBI将仅在'计划规范'和'计划过程'类下进行子类划分和工作，以避免深入讨论'意图'等。</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">branch derived</obo:IAO_0000119> <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="zh">分支派生</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">plan</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">计划</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000379 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000379">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000034"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A mechanical function is a function that is realised via mechanical work (through an certain amount of energy transferred by some force).</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">机械功能是通过机械功（通过某种力传递一定量的能量）实现的功能。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="en">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanical_work</obo:IAO_0000119> <obo:IAO_0000119 xml:lang="zh">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanical_work</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mechanical function</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">机械功能</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000571 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000571">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom>
                    <owl:Class>
                        <owl:unionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606"/>
                            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000245"/>
                        </owl:unionOf>
                    </owl:Class>
                </owl:someValuesFrom>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="en">With respect to The Accuri C6 Flow Cytometer System, the organization Accuri bears the role manufacturer role.  With respect to a transformed line of tissue culture cells derived by a specific lab, the lab whose personnel isolated the cll line bears the role manufacturer role.  With respect to a specific antibody produced by an individual scientist, the scientist who purifies, characterizes and distributes the anitbody bears the role manufacturer role.</obo:IAO_0000112> <obo:IAO_0000112 xml:lang="zh">对于Accuri C6流式细胞仪系统，组织Accuri承担制造商角色。对于由特定实验室衍生的转化组织培养细胞系，其人员分离该细胞系的实验室承担制造商角色。对于由个别科学家生产的特定抗体，纯化、表征和分发该抗体的科学家承担制造商角色。</obo:IAO_0000112>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Manufacturer role is a role which inheres in a person or organization and which is realized by a manufacturing process.</obo:IAO_0000115> <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="zh">制造商角色是内在于个人或组织并通过制造过程实现的一种角色。</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>OBI</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">manufacturer role</rdfs:label> <rdfs:label xml:lang="zh">制造商角色</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000835 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000835">
        <owl:equivalentClass>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
